OT	Mac and Cheese
OT	Vegetarian Times Issue: June 1, 2008 p.71
OT	Print-Friendly Version
OT	Email to a Friend
OT	The “cheese” sauce is thickened with rice flour, making it both vegan and gluten free. This recipe was a winner in our 2008 Restaurant Poll, and is a popular entrée at the kid-friendly Vita Café in Portland, Oregon.
OT	Directions
OT	Whisk together soymilk, rice flour, yeast, soy sauce, granulated garlic, and granulated onion in saucepan. Simmer 4 minutes, or until thickened, whisking constantly. Whisk in margarine and mustard, and simmer 10 minutes more.
OT	Cook pasta according to package directions. Drain, and toss with sauce.
